summary: whatdo you think when people say dan and phil don’t give fan service? do you think dan and phil are just doing what they want?
question: whatdo you think when people say dan and phil don’t give fan service? do you think dan and phil are just doing what they want?
answer: If a person says that Dan and Phil don’t give fanservice, they are extremely naive, choosing to live in a fantasy world, or intentionally trying to mislead others. Dan and Phil are professional entertainers, of course they give fan service. Everything we see from them is heavily edited and curated. They know who their audience are, what we want to see, and how what they do in their videos and on social media will impact their income. Technically they are doing what they want because no one is holding a gun to their head, but it’s been a long time since YouTube was full of kids making videos in their dorm room as if the camera wasn’t rolling. Dan and Phil have become quite good at “giving the people what they want” over the years and have made a ton of money doing it. Enjoy their content, but enjoy it for what it is and don’t confuse it for a raw look into their private lives and who they are when the cameras are turned off.
